/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1239%2C826 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1859%2C1239 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=407%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=815%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1223%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1631%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=407%2C271, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=815%2C543 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1223%2C815 3x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1631%2C1087 4x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?webp=true&amp;quality=45&amp;resize=1667%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/webp\"><source media=\"(min-width: 590px)\" data-srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=555%2C370, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1110%2C740 2x, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=1667%2C1111 3x\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img data-src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\" width=\"620\" height=\"413\" alt=\"WTB Venture TCS 650b x 47 tubeless ready tyres on Prime Kanza wheels\" title=\"WTB Venture TCS 650b x 47 tubeless ready tyres on Prime Kanza wheels\" src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_016_1-794b2ad.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=620%2C413\"></picture></div><div><figcaption><span><i></i> The WTB Venture TCS 650b x 47 tubeless-ready tyres and Prime Kanza wheels look like a great combination on paper.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Russel Burton / Immediate Media</i></span></p></div><p>The drivetrain is made up of <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/news/sram-apex-1-brings-1x-road-to-affordable-level/\">SRAM’s 11-speed Apex 1x groupset</a>, with a KMC chain and 11-42 tooth SunTour cassette substituted in.</p><p>The SRAM Apex X-Sync 1x chainset is fitted with a 40t chainring, giving a decent spread of gears for general on- and off-road riding, and the rear derailleur has a clutch mechanism to help keep the chain in check.</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/buyers-guides/gravel-bike-setup/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Gravel bike setup: how to choose the right gearing, wheel size, tyres and more</a></li></ul><div><p><i title=\"Enlarge photo\" data-slide-index=\"1\">Enlarge photo</i></p><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 375px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 425px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 600px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 767px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 991px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_001_1-ae24c4e.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960%2C640\" alt=\"SRAM Apex hydraulic gear and brake lever\" height=\"640\" width=\"960\"></picture><div><p><i><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><title>icon / camera</title><g fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M10 12.08a1.6 1.6 0 1 1 0-3.204 1.6 1.6 0 0 1 0 3.204m0-4.457a2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0 5.711 2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0-5.71\" fill=\"#343434\"></path><path d=\"M16.036 13.23c0 .682-.553 1.234-1.234 1.234H5.199a1.234 1.234 0 0 1-1.234-1.234V7.623c0-.639.518-1.157 1.157-1.157h2.315l.11-.46a1.578 1.578 0 0 1 1.536-1.22h1.837c.734 0 1.37.505 1.537 1.22l.106.46h2.315c.64 0 1.158.518 1.158 1.157v5.607zM10 0C4.478 0 0 4.477 0 10s4.478 10 10 10c5.523 0 10-4.477 10-10S15.523 0 10 0z\" fill=\"#000\"></path></g></svg></i></p><figcaption><span>SRAM Apex hydraulic gear and brake lever.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Russel Burton / Immediate Media</i></span></p></div></div></div>The finishing kit is also by Vitus, and consists mostly of good quality aluminium parts that help keep the price down and should prove reliable over the long term.<p>The handlebar is notably progressive too, with flattened tops to improve comfort and flared drops for improved control off-road.</p><div><p><i title=\"Enlarge photo\" data-slide-index=\"1\">Enlarge photo</i></p><div><picture><source media=\"(max-width: 320px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 375px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 425px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 600px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 767px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(max-width: 991px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><source media=\"(min-width: 992px)\" type=\"image/jpeg\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2021/02/vitus__substance_srs_russ_b_002_1-ca1a2c8.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=960%2C640\" alt=\"Vitus Substance SRS 1 cockpit\" height=\"640\" width=\"960\"></picture><div><p><i><svg width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><title>icon / camera</title><g fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M10 12.08a1.6 1.6 0 1 1 0-3.204 1.6 1.6 0 0 1 0 3.204m0-4.457a2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0 5.711 2.856 2.856 0 0 0 0-5.71\" fill=\"#343434\"></path><path d=\"M16.036 13.23c0 .682-.553 1.234-1.234 1.234H5.199a1.234 1.234 0 0 1-1.234-1.234V7.623c0-.639.518-1.157 1.157-1.157h2.315l.11-.46a1.578 1.578 0 0 1 1.536-1.22h1.837c.734 0 1.37.505 1.537 1.22l.106.46h2.315c.64 0 1.158.518 1.158 1.157v5.607zM10 0C4.478 0 0 4.477 0 10s4.478 10 10 10c5.523 0 10-4.477 10-10S15.523 0 10 0z\" fill=\"#000\"></path></g></svg></i></p><figcaption><span>The aluminium Vitus handlebar features flattened tops and flared drops.</span></figcaption><p><span><i>Russel Burton / Immediate Media</i></span></p></div></div></div>The Substance SRS1 is available in six sizes, from XS to XXL. According to Vitus, these sizes should cater for cyclists ranging in height from 155cm up to 200cm.<p>The <a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/advice/sizing-and-fit/road-bike-geometry-explained/\">geometry</a> is fairly relaxed, with a size medium frame having a stack and reach of 567.5mm and 381.9mm, respectively. The 73.5-degree seat-tube angle and a slack 71.5-degree head-tube angle, paired with a 90mm stem (smaller and larger sizes get correspondingly shorter and longer stems), should provide a calm and confident steering response.</p><p>Vitus says “the Substance is the bike that will go anywhere you point it; on whatever surface you choose”, and we’re very much looking forward to putting that claim to the test.</p></section><section><h3>Authors</h3><section><a href=\"https://www.bikeradar.com/author/bromleysimon/\"><img src=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=60,60\" srcset=\"https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=45&amp;resize=120,120 120w, https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/21/2020/06/Simon-Bromley_Profile-Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585-d34f7eb-scaled.jpg?quality=90&amp;resize=60,60 60w,\" sizes=\"(max-width: 60px) 100vw, 60px\" width=\"60\" height=\"60\" alt=\"Simon Bromley_Profile Pic\" title=\"Simon Bromley_Profile Pic_2020_04_12_IMG_4585\"></a><p>Simon is a writer and photographer who has been riding bikes for fun since he was a kid. He took a deep dive into road racing, crits and time trial culture in his twenties, but as a person of very little talent, he always looks to tech to compensate. He loves nothing more than finding a smart (preferably cheap) hack that others hadn’t thought of. His stable of bikes isn’t the most extravagant, but they’re all customised to meet Simon’s particular tastes and kept fastidiously clean.</p></section></section></div>","author":"Simon Bromley","siteTitle":"BikeRadar","siteHash":"df99dd1320fcd97327a2def4c67247c08cd4090a7dab684a0eddb9b856f80ef1","entryHash":"f80327c3dd7d9a8019a4ad56122e8a333414c3deeef656efa3ab224670452191","category":"Cycling"}